  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav) translates to \"discrimination\" or \"differentiation\" in English. It refers to the unfair treatment or distinction made against individuals or groups based on certain characteristics such as race, gender, caste, religion, or socioeconomic status. The term is often used in discussions about social justice, equality, and human rights.",
